					<description><![CDATA[<p>Series A Funding Accelerates Airspeed’s Global Expansion Airspeed has raised $20 million in Series A funding led by DN Capital. The company runs between London and New York, zeroing in</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/airspeed-raises-20m-series-a-revenue-execution/" data-wpel-link="internal">Airspeed Raises $20M Series A to Scale Agent-Native Revenue Execution Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Series A Funding Accelerates Airspeed’s Global Expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Airspeed has raised $20 million in Series A funding led by DN Capital. The company runs between London and New York, zeroing in on enterprise revenue automation. After this round, they&#8217;ve pulled in over $25 million in funding. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">That&#8217;s money they&#8217;re putting into product development, hiring, and breaking further into the US market. Investors like Vi Partners, Framework Venture Partners, and Atlassian Ventures jumped in, adding their enterprise and SaaS experience to the mix. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">They started out as Glyphic back in 2022, but switched to Airspeed in 2026.  That new name? It’s all about moving from just building tools to actually driving results for revenue teams. Airspeed now pitches itself as an execution-first platform, not just another analytics add-on. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors are clearly noticing DN Capital led the round, and they&#8217;ve got a track record for picking leaders in new markets. The excitement around this autonomous workflow system is definitely picking up.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Agents Built for Revenue Execution Workflows</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Airspeed creates an execution layer for revenue teams that transforms conversations into actions. Airspeed integrates all communications, calls, CRM data and support tickets – into a single system. Autonomous AI agents act across communication channels, updating systems, sending follow-ups, and detecting risks without human intervention.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Traditional enterprise software is designed around dashboards and reports.These tools show what is happening but do not complete the work. Airspeed targets this gap by enabling direct execution across revenue workflows. The platform ensures that commercial context is converted into operational action. This reduces manual coordination across sales and customer systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The system operates across the full revenue lifecycle of an organisation. It supports deal tracking, customer communication, and CRM updates in one layer. Customers have built thousands of custom agents across the platform. Usage has grown rapidly, with monthly activity nearly tripling in early 2026. </span><a href="https://www.investopedia.com/terms/r/revenue.asp" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Revenue</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has also increased fourfold over the past twelve months.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A real-world example comes from enterprise software company Foleon. The company saved more than $193,000 using Airspeed within 90 days. It also reclaimed six hours per sales representative each week. These results highlight measurable efficiency gains in enterprise sales operations. Adoption continues across 200 customers in 20 countries.</span></p>
<h2><b>Founding Team, Research Depth, and Global Expansion</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202404" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202404" class="size-full wp-image-202404" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Airspeed-2.png" alt="Illustration of AI automation in healthcare clinics, showing administrative tasks being replaced by intelligent systems that improve efficiency and patient care across medical practices." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202404" class="wp-caption-text">Growing adoption of AI automation in healthcare is transforming administrative workflows, enabling clinics to reduce operational burdens, improve efficiency, and focus more on patient care as demand for autonomous systems accelerates. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Airspeed was founded by Adam Liska and Devang Agrawal, both former DeepMind researchers. Liska has worked across DeepMind, Spotify, Facebook, and IBM with a focus on machine learning. He also holds a PhD in Brain and Cognitive Sciences, which informs his systems approach. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Agrawal studied engineering at the University of Cambridge and received the Dr Manmohan Singh Scholarship. He later worked at Apple and co-founded a youth science network in India. The company has expanded its engineering team across London and New York. It has hired talent from Meta, Apple, and Spotify to scale its technical operations. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Headcount has doubled over the past year as enterprise demand increased. The team focuses on building reliable AI systems for real-time execution. Their approach combines research depth with commercial deployment discipline. Airspeed was designed around the idea that insight alone is no longer enough. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Enterprise software improved visibility over the past decade but left an execution manual. The platform aims to close this gap by automating workflow actions directly. Its agents operate on live commercial context instead of static dashboards. This enables continuous execution across revenue systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/lassie-raises-35m-ai-small-business-automation/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Lassie Raises $35M to Expand Autonomous AI for Small Businesses</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Competitive Landscape and Enterprise AI Market Growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Airspeed operates in a competitive enterprise AI market that is evolving quickly. Companies like Gong, Salesloft, and Outreach dominate revenue intelligence and engagement. These platforms focus on insights, conversation tracking, and workflow support. However, execution remains partially manual across most systems today.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">11x has also raised $50 million in Series B funding for AI sales agents. The company focuses on autonomous outbound sales and pipeline generation. This highlights growing competition in agent-based revenue automation. Airspeed differentiates itself by focusing on a unified execution layer. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It connects conversations, data, and backend systems into one operational flow. The global AI in the sales market was valued at $24.64 billion in 2024. It is projected to reach $145.12 billion by 2033, growing at a CAGR of 22.2 percent. Growth is driven by demand for automation that goes beyond analytics. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Companies are shifting toward systems that actively perform work. This trend supports the rise of execution-focused AI platforms. DN Capital has previously backed companies like Shazam, Auto1, and Remitly. Its investment in Airspeed reflects confidence in enterprise AI automation. The firm sees execution layers as the next evolution of SaaS infrastructure. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">However, competition from larger enterprise vendors remains a key challenge. Salesforce and Gong continue to expand their AI capabilities aggressively. Airspeed’s long-term position depends on speed of execution and adoption. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is building infrastructure for autonomous revenue workflows. Its goal is to become the system that connects insight directly to action. This positions it at the centre of the next enterprise software shift.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/airspeed-raises-20m-series-a-revenue-execution/" data-wpel-link="internal">Airspeed Raises $20M Series A to Scale Agent-Native Revenue Execution Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
