		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 09:30:16 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=202378</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Merantix Capital, Europe&#8217;s premier AI investor, has announced the final closing of its second fund, a €103 million fundraising which will be used to break through as Europe&#8217;s industrial expertise</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/merantix-capital-launches-e103m-fund-for-european-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal">Merantix Capital Launches €103M Fund for European AI</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.merantix-capital.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Merantix Capital</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, Europe&#8217;s premier AI investor, has announced the final closing of its second </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/quobly-closes-e115m-series-a-for-quantum-growth/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">fund</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, a €103 million fundraising which will be used to break through as Europe&#8217;s industrial expertise directly enters first-mover AI-native companies. The new capital fund more than tripled the size of the first €30 million vehicle.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This venture capital firm based out of Berlin and London is expected to use these funds to support some 40 early-stage AI startups across Europe. The fund aims to act as a conduit between &#8216;mature European industries&#8217; and &#8216;the world of machine learning&#8217;.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Hybrid Investment Architecture</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">What sets the newly launched vehicle apart is its pioneering 50/50 allocation model. Merantix Capital apportions its capital evenly across two separate streams of early-stage venture building. The first is investing in its own venture studio, where 50% of the €103 million will be funnelled. For this stream, Merantix partners with technical founders through the pre-idea state to validate ideas and create prototypes within the tools of the in-house infrastructure.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202379" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202379" class="size-large wp-image-202379" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/AI-1-1024x576.jpg" alt="AI" width="1024" height="576" /><p id="caption-attachment-202379" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The other 50% of the fund is a significant strategic development for the firm. </span>Merantix set aside the fund for direct external investments into native, pre-seed and seed-stage independent AI companies throughout Europe. It anticipates cheque sizes of between €1m and €3m per deal. Merantix expanded its scope from an exclusively venture studio-focused incubator of in-house ideas to a broader European-focused incubator of both in-house ideas and AI startups.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/quobly-closes-e115m-series-a-for-quantum-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Quobly Closes €115M Series A for Quantum Growth</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Deep Alignment with Industrial Verticals</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Compared to venture funds that support broad horizontal AI products, such as consumer-focused large language models or a general, horizontal AI application, Merantix specialises in deep, specific industry use cases. The fund focuses on industries that fit into the European economy&#8217;s established footprint, mainly logistics, advanced manufacturing, energy systems, healthcare and life sciences, physical AI, and robotics.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The central insight is to firmly implant machine learning into vertical supply chains and workflows where automation is a solution to short-term chokepoints. In the machine-learning industry, Luminar has garnered an impressive roster of institutional LP investors, corporate allies, and foundations. Among these backers are the asset manager Union Investment, a manufacturer of logistics equipment called Jungheinrich, KPMG Germany, the Robert Wood Johnson Foundation, and the W.K. Kellogg Foundation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The fund also acts as a tool for digital transformation for corporate limited partners, such as Jungheinrich and KPMG. Corporate partners benefit from first-mover access to pilots, new automation opportunities, and integration into the Masalaekos network.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Active Deployment and Ecosystem Support</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Merantix is making investments from the new fund into a few early teams. Early public investments include Droidrun, a startup building infrastructure for mobile native AI agents; Arqh, an AI-powered logistics optimisation SaaS; and Outpost Bio, a company specialising in using machine learning for human microbiology. Other early investments include a handful of undisclosed stealth mode projects across recruitment tech, enterprise resource planning, fashion tech and manufacturing.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Funded startups gain direct access to Merantix&#8217;s extensive network, including the Merantix AI Campus in Berlin, a physical ecosystem with over 80 companies and hundreds of annual technical events, the London AI Hub and AI House Davos. Infrastructure enables portfolio companies to connect with commercial partners, technical validation and world-class machine learning engineering talent.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/merantix-capital-launches-e103m-fund-for-european-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal">Merantix Capital Launches €103M Fund for European AI</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
